ncludes the correct line.","test_description":"Create a temp file with invalid YAML (e.g., missing colon on line 3), call the loader on that file, catch the exception, and assert the error message includes 'line 3' (or the correct line number from the real parser).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test requires actual YAML parsing to catch error-message formatting bugs; mocks would pass even if line number is missing or wrong.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the config directory does not exist at startup, the loader creates it and writes a defaults file before proceeding.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is incomplete file system state: directory created but file not written, file written to wrong path, permissions prevent creation, or the loader errors instead of creating. Mocking os.makedirs() or open() would hide these failures. Must verify the actual directory and file exist on disk after the loader runs. Requires real file system operations.","test_description":"Start with a temp directory where the config subdirectory does not exist, call the loader with that temp directory, and assert the directory and defaults file actually exist on the file system and contain expected default content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test requires verifying real files on disk; mocks would hide file creation failures or permission issues.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13512,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13512},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65bdf08